  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Ellicott's Commentary for English Readers",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "(17, 18) ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "Then said some of his disciples among themselves.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "—Better, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Therefore said",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " . . . The question arises out of what He has said. They draw aside and discuss the matter privately. It is beyond their comprehension, and seems to be contradictory.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "A little while, and ye shall not see me.—Better, A little while, and ye behold Me not, as in John 16:16.",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "bld",
            "text": "A little while, and ye shall not see me.",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "—Better, ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "ital",
            "text": "A little while, and ye behold Me not,",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " as in ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "John 16:16",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ".",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Because I go to the Father.—So far they have quoted word for word what He had said in the previous verse. They now connect it with what He had said in John 16:7; John 16:10, and this forms the ground of their surprise. There He had spoken of their beholding Him no more because He goeth to the Father. Here He speaks of a little while, after which they shall not behold Him, and again a little while, after which they shall see Him. They cannot reconcile these things. They cannot tell what He saith.",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "bld",
            "text": "Because I go to the Father.",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "—So far they have quoted word for word what He had said in the previous verse. They now connect it with what He had said in ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "John 16:7",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "; ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "John 16:10",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ", and this forms the ground of their surprise. There He had spoken of their beholding Him no more because He goeth to the Father. Here He speaks of a little while, after which they shall not behold Him, and again a little while, after which they shall see Him. They cannot reconcile these things. They cannot tell what He saith.",
            "children": []
